    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all thirteen V&V 40 factors and determined that the overall evidence base supports an Accepted outcome. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is offset by the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, the direct QoI correspondence, and the demonstrated convergence of the FEA ensemble. The E/uval metric and percent difference criteria were satisfied for all three QoIs. The model is accepted for use in the stated COU.",
